  ('Landmine Romanian Deadlift to Row', 'landmine-romanian-deadlift-to-row', 'Perform Landmine Romanian Deadlift to Row as a landmine-based hinge pull pattern. The athlete uses the fixed angled bar path to create useful load while maintaining bracing, breathing, grip ownership, and a repeatable finish position.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 6, 20, 75, 30, 'Landmine Romanian Deadlift to Row is a landmine exercise for hinge strength plus row finish for posterior chain, lats, and bracing. Use it when the goal is quality force, posture, and repeatable bar path rather than fatigue chasing.', 'Primary subrole: hinge_posterior_chain_strength. Coach the athlete to earn load through setup, grip, stance, trunk pressure, and bar-path repeatability before chasing heavier plates or faster reps.', 'Own the position first, move the bar second, and stop before the shape changes.', 'Rows and Pulls', 'capacity', 'hinge_posterior_chain_strength', 'landmine_landmine_romanian_deadlift_to_row', '{"primary_joint_actions":["scapular_retraction_depression","shoulder_extension","elbow_flexion","hip_hinge_hold","hip_hinge","posterior_chain_tension","spinal_bracing","grip_closure","wrist_neutral_control"],"primary_tissues":["forearm","hip","upper_back","core","hamstring"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"moderate_bracing_with_controlled_exhale","balance_demand":"moderate","coordination_demand":"high","impact_level":0,"grip_profile":{"type":"handle_grip","attachment":"neutral_handle_or_v_handle","wristRule":"neutral, pain-free wrist; choose ball or handle only when it improves control."}}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"hold a hinge position, then row the landmine without changing spinal position","setup":["Anchor the bar in a secure landmine base or immovable corner that cannot slide.","Load the bar conservatively and make sure the sleeve path is clear.","Attach the handle, V-handle, or neutral grip securely and confirm it matches the intended wrist positio